  [Text] Bolivia and Brazil today signed a new bilateral 
agreement. Brazilian Foreign Minister Celso Amorim arrived in 
our country to sign it. 
  It should be recalled that Bolivia and Brazil signed a 
partial agreement in 1983. The new agreement not only grants 
preferential tariffs -- which involve reduced taxes on imports 
-- but also provides for business cooperation and the exchange 
of commercial information. 
  [Begin Bolivian Foreign Minister Antonio Aranibar recording] 
It proves the fruitful talks and exchange of viewpoints that we 
maintained during an active day with Foreign Minister Amorim. 
