   By STEPHEN FIDLER, Latin America Editor


The state oil companies of Brazil and Bolivia have put out to international
tender a contract to supply equipment and services for the planned
Brazil-Bolivia gas pipe line.
Work on the first stage of the pipeline, from Rio Grande in Bolivia to Porto
Alegre in Brazil, is expected to start next August. The project is expected
to use 2,200km of pipeline and will cost Dollars 2.2bn.
The pipeline should provide income of Dollars 200m a year for Bolivia. The
two companies have already selected a number of large international
companies as strategic partners in the project.


